The paper focuses on optimizing the collaboration between human supervisors and robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the cognitive resources and attention of the human supervisor, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of reachability theory to construct safe sets for the robots falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The paper proposes a method that uses machine learning to decrease false positives, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
